cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.MA, cs.DS 

This paper deals with logic and reasoning about knowledge and strategies in multi-agent systems, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) since the paper introduces a new logic framework for reasoning about knowledge and strategies. The paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) since it deals with multi-agent systems and their decision-making processes. Game theory (cs.GT) is another likely category since the paper uses concurrent game models to provide semantics to the logic framework. Multi-agent systems (cs.MA) is also a relevant category since the paper deals with reasoning about agents and their interactions. Finally, the paper involves some computational complexity analysis, which could place it under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
